          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want articles written, optimized, and published — without a stack?</h4>
            <p>Book a 20-minute demo. We'll show you how theStacc replaces Surfer + Jasper + WordPress workflow with <strong>one $99/mo subscription</strong>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See the demo <span>&rarr;</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">20 min · No card</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is AI SEO software?</h2>
        <p>AI SEO software is any platform that uses AI to automate a step of the SEO process. The category covers four jobs today:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Research</strong> — keyword discovery, SERP analysis, competitor gap (Semrush, Ahrefs, SE Ranking).</li>
          <li><strong>Generation</strong> — long-form draft writing tuned for brand voice (Jasper, Scalenut, Copy.ai).</li>
          <li><strong>Optimization</strong> — scoring drafts against SERP top results (Surfer, Frase, Clearscope, MarketMuse).</li>
          <li><strong>Publishing</strong> — pushing finished articles into your CMS with structure intact (theStacc, SEO.AI).</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Most "AI SEO software" lists conflate these jobs. They are not interchangeable — buying Jasper does not get you optimization, and buying Surfer does not get you a writer. The buyers who win pick by job, not brand.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">Watch for these red flags</div>
          <p>Avoid any vendor that <strong>(a)</strong> claims "complete SEO automation" without specifying publishing, <strong>(b)</strong> caps articles per month but hides the cap behind "credits," or <strong>(c)</strong> insists on an annual contract for a tool you have not seen produce a single published piece. Real publishing platforms show you live customer sites on the demo.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 platforms</h2>
        <p>To keep the comparison fair, every platform was given the same brief: produce, optimize, and publish 6 articles on the same target keywords across the same test sites.</p>

